  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-Saving, Multi-Sectoral Emergency Assistance and Protection to Vulnerable Displaced Persons in Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ethiopia continues to have one of the most complex operating environments for humanitarian intervention in the world. Natural and man-made disasters continue to affect Ethiopia on an increasing scale. IOM provide critical multi-sector humanitarian assistance to displaced persons across Ethiopia, with some interventions specifically targeting Tigray. The action provides material assistance, such as water and site care and maintenance through integrated protection programming as well as including post-arrival services to forced returnees from the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia (KSA). IOM is further strengthening the capacity of the humanitarian aid system to provide timely and targeted humanitarian assistance through information management, assessing and disseminating multi-sectoral information on displacement and protection needs, cluster coordination and capacity building on prevention from sexual exploitation and abuse and complaints and feedback mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
